parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Caliper Freeze and Brake Fluid Boil Over
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of brakes can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving on downhill grades or in emergency braking situations.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brakes
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
smoke or burning smell from the brakes
brake warning indicator illuminates on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent brake failure can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds or in emergency braking situations.
symptoms: Intermittent loss of brakes
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake warning indicator illuminates on the instrument panel
brake failure occurs after hard stops or prolonged braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure Due to Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the brake system can cause brake failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake failure
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake warning indicator illuminates on the instrument panel
brake failure occurs after hard stops or prolonged braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, especially at high speeds, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls intermittently
the vehicle loses power
the "Reduce Power" warning light illuminates
the vehicle experiences a severe jolt while traveling at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the engine cooling system can cause overheating, leading to engine damage, and potentially causing a fire.
symptoms: The heater grid
part of the engine cooling system
fails to turn off
causing the wire to burn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially if the stall occurs at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the vehicle is difficult to start
the vehicle experiences a loss of power
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise.
